76561198025011010,Recommended,229480,8133078,"Posted: 19 December, 2013",all,StrangeApe,"Chronicles of Mystara is a classic arcade brawler from the 90s.  It contains two games, Tower of Doom and Shadow Over Mystara.  They are remarkable in that they both stand up remarkably well for being nearly 20 years old.  Branching paths, level ups, weapon upgrades, shopping...  Basically these games, for their time, and even now, do a fantastic job of capturing much of the Dungeons and Dragons formula.That being said, these games run on the Advanced Dungeons and Dragons (AD&D) rules, so if you play a character who casts spells, don't expect to be able to blast away willy-nilly.  Spells a ultra-powerful abilities that are extremely limited in their use until the party makes camp for the night, and this only happens at set story moments in the game.  You don't get to choose.All in all, it's a fantastic game."
76561198051242041,Recommended,229480,17164977,"Posted: 21 July, 2015",all,Donoknight,"Dungeons&Dragons is something that I really enjoy (am I a Dungeon Master). Even though this game is slightly old, it still has very good playablility. The game itself is set in Mystara which is a unknown/unique D&D world, or basically what is known as a Home Campaign. Anyway, enough of the basics, lets write out the pros and cons.Pros-Graphics, the graphics are actually pretty good (for the time that is). The characters and things look cool, and have many different animations.Character Development, although there is a set number of characters you can play as, as to how you use them is totally up to you. Want to have a Dwarf tank while using only ranged weapons? You can do that (albeit unnatural). Plus your characters level up the more you use them, so playing the game through with a single character is ideal here.Music/Audio, the music is really good, but the audio is really good. From the clang of weapon on shield to the hit of a spell on an enemy, it just sounds cool.Cons-Difficulty, unless you play this game a lot, then you will likely think the difficulty to be overly hard. But you must remember that this was an arcade game, where they made it hard so you would have to dish money into them. If you get good at it, it actually isn't to hard, just keep at it.Class Balancing, although each class has its own unique things, the classes overall are not balanced. The mage by far is overpowered, with so many spells available to him and so many uses for such spells, you can basically walk through almost all the levels. But the real over powered character is the Warrior. If you get good at using him, he can basically defeat anything given enough time.Menu, using a keyboard is not recommended, it is just to inefficient to try to cycle through the menus while avoiding a Displacer Beast or Beholder.Conclusion-Overall, it is still a very fun and challenging game. If you like old style arcade games and hack and slash games, then this is a must. If you like anything Dungeons&Dragons, then you may be interested in the story, much like myself. Anyway, hope this review has helped at least a little bit.May your adventures be many and always end in reward!-Donoknight, Founder of Tabletop RPG Gamers League"
