,Recommended,229480,7808168,"Posted: 28 November, 2013",all,X Kirby,"Definitely an Arcade game, it has a crapton of features for a Beat-Em-Up. In total there's 100 items across 2 seperate games! Mix that with new ""House Rules"" and local/online drop-in/drop-out multiplayer for up to 4 players and you've got a game that's worth the $15 in my eyes.The combat system is pretty basic, but each of the 6 characters are indeed in-depth enough to make things interesting. Unless you're the Magic-User, combo potential is pretty good for beating down your opponents. The Magic-User can also combo, but not to the same degree of depth. Spells make up for this though, and BOY does he have a lot of them.Unsurprisingly, this game has a Level-Up system. The Score you gain from grabbing items and killing enemies are the Experience Points you gain for leveling-up, which increases your Health and makes you more powerful to some degree. I mean, it's Dungeons & Dragons, so it's kind of expected, even if it doesn't make too much sense for a Beat-Em-Up.The game is kind of unforgiving in terms of difficulty, so expect to die a lot. I got game over 30+ times during my 1st and 2nd playthrough of Shadow over Mystara. I haven't tried online play yet, but I hope to if my friends pick the game up. Maybe more players will make it easier, although I doubt it. This still won't deter me from playing it!All I can say is, if you're a fan of old-school Arcade Beat-Em-Ups, you'd be missing out on a gem if you've never played this."
