76561198040084487,Recommended,229480,18376812,"Posted: 7 October, 2015",all,atarumenchi,"Arcade beat-em-up at its best.I can't stress how much fun this game is, even single-player.  The game itself is challenging and engrossing, just like it was back in the arcade years.ratings are from 1-5Gameplay: 5 - No complex formulas.  No intriquet combo systems.  Just pure basic hack-n-slash gameplay of the arcade straight to your steam account and onto your PC.  It's a great romp from start to finish and includes not just other characters, but difficulty settings to keep you coming back for more and pit you against more challenigng enemies.  Discover each character's abilities and level them up by yourself or with local and online co-op (finding people to play this online is a challenge, as not many people set up lobbies for this).Sound: 5 - Nostalgia-city for most arcade-goers in the 90s.  The music and sounds are spot-on and have aged fairly well.  All the yelling, grunting, and character voices are all here.Graphics: 4.5 - The grapihcs get the job done with vibrant colors and great special effects.  Still, you may get bored looking at some of the same browns and greys, but each environment differs from the other in some way, making it not so bland.Control: 4.5 - The controls are flawless, but it does require learing which keys/buttons do what commands.  Still, with a 360 controller, it's nearly a walk in the park.  Using magic, items and having to select them can be a pain, especially in the heat of battle, but it still works and remember: this is an arcade port.Overall: 4.75 - Even solo, I find myself coming back and visiting Mysteria over and over again.  Though I only have 2 hours put into this game, I've been playing it since I got it a bit at a time.  I first finished the game with the cleric, and am currently working on the elf as of this writing.For those wishing to take a trip down memory lane, it's well worth the price.  Those looking for an interesting 4-player beat-em-up and have a few local friends to play with, it's definitely worth it.  Fans of hack-n-slash games will also find some enjoyment and there are unlockable items only attainable by purchasing with in-game currency earned while playing."
