76561197961812555,Recommended,229480,12086874,"Posted: 13 September, 2014",all,It's For Free,"Fantastic value for what you are getting.  If you ever played it in the arcade there were never enough quarters in the world to get you through.  Now that is no longer a problem and with full online co-op support with drop in and drop out you can play with your friends  from anywhere without having to both be sitting in front of the same screen.  Oustanding port by Capcom that does not lose anything from the original.My only complaint (and maybe I just have not figured out how to adjust this yet) is the sounds of the actual heroes in the game.  They are EXTREMELY quiet compared to the arcade cabinet.  In the arcade me and my friends would always be parroting their ridiculous quotes like the infamous ""LIGHTNING BOLT"" as the characters say whatever spell they are casting out loud.  That was a huge part of the fun of this game was the extremely silly voice acting of the characters shouting out the names of spells as they were casting them.  It is very hard to hear them over the battle sound effects that are going on as you are almost always in large fights in the game.For $14.99 its a steal- as it includes both of the full arcade games.  If you can get it on sale (I nailed it for the $7.99) it is a stupidly good deal for the play through value you will get.DO NOT buy this game for single player as it just feels extremely lonely and wrong to try and play it by yourself with a single hero.  You need at least 2+ people to truly enjoy this arcade masterpiece."
