,Recommended,229480,7462982,"Posted: 23 October, 2013",all,"Big Blake, Towering Bruiser","I first played this game in my town's arcade when I was a wee little tyke, so maybe I'm looking through some rose-tinted glasses here, but I love this game. ""Shadow Over Mystara"" specifically, since this includes both Shadows, and ""Tower of Doom"". The controls if you're using a keyboard are rather wonky, so I highly recommend using a controller. If you've played either of these games before, you know what you're getting. My favorite option though is the inclusion of a scan lines options and removing the HD smoothness for that pure nostaglia feel. If you're looking for a new age beat'em go play Dragon's Crown, this game is still fantastic, but it is dated."
,Recommended,229480,560147,"Posted: 28 June, 2013",all,Qviss,"A Shadow of Mystara reviewAt first, this game might seem bland and out of balanced, yet if you give it some time you discover how much fun it can be, that is, if you like the genre. For a beat em up you have tons of variety in spells, items, classes and different paths you can take on, adding lots of replayability. It should be noted, that some people have some crashing experiences in the main menu, but I haven't heard anyone dropping from the game yet, so all things considered, it gets a pass in my book.Multiplayer is for up to 4 players and there is 6 classes to choose from: Fighter, dwarf, elf, cleric, thief and magic user. They have some of the basic things in common, like basic combo and slide, but there is major differences in how they actually play. For example, dwarf has a lots of tankiness but is somewhat slow, while thief is weaker but can backstab, double jump and steal items.Game rewards people for teamwork, and a right team saves of a lot of continues, since every class is tailored for something: Fighter, dwarf and thief are good for killing standard mobs, while cleric has a heal and stat boosting abilities, lastly Magic user and elf are useful for killing bosses. This doesn't mean you can't solo the game with any class without dying once if you have played it enough and know it's gimmicks.At the moment of this recommendation, there is a a few players in online, so you still have a chance to play this on multiplayer even if you can't get your friends to play this. This game is made in 1993, however, it has aged well since it was made for the arcade board. Just remember to change filters and resolution from the options first.For a nitpick, I'd say it is a bit on the easy side, because you get unlimited credits by default. You can later change survival mode on, which causes everyone to have only one life, but it would've been better, if you could set the amount of credits yourself.With it's good replayability, animation and presentation, this title was a classic of it's time and before Dragon's Crown comes out, it doesn't get better than this."
