,Recommended,229480,24236302,"Posted: 10 July, 2016",all,unknowncity,"It's a fun enough beat-em-up. I remember the old arcade game, and just what a quarter-eating beast it was. Picking this up on sale for $5 is definitely preferable to the $15 I would have spent at the arcade trying to get to the end. Relative to other brawler games from the era, there is some depth to this one. That said, even with the range of character options and branching story paths, it's still a short game (I beat both campaigns in about 4 hours) with a lot of repetitive action. There are better games for $15, but if you're nostalgic for the old arcade game, it's worth picking this up on sale."
