76561198352634058,Recommended,229480,29308688,Posted: 16 January,all,Bagalagalaga,"If I could have told myself 20 years ago at Chuckie Cheeses that one day this arcade game would be available at my very own home....I still would have blown $10 worth of tokens trying to beat a boss. It loses a lot of the urgency to play well when you can just continue infinitely, but its fun to hack and slash through, and finally see the whole game past the first 2-3  stages.I thought it was pretty much only for nostalgic types, but the kids have got on and played through it as well and seemed to like it as a change of pace. It's not going to keep you occupied for 50 hours, but it is a fun and pretty quick playthrough. Probably not popular enough to remaster, so you've got the classic, very dated graphics."
